This PR adds support for parsing static initializer blocks:

```javascript
class Example{
  static attrib;
  static {
   this.attrib = "exampleValue";
  }
}
```

and "for await ... of ..." loops:

```javascript
async function* foo() {
  yield 1;
  yield 2;
}

(async function() {
  for await (const num of foo()) {
    console.log(num);   // expected output: 1
    break;              // closes iterator, triggers return
  }
})();
```

Closes: #4262
Closes: #4757

- https://github.com/apache/netbeans/issues/5186

e.g.
```php
match(true){
	'test' => [
		'key' => 'value',
		],
};
```

Before: An array is broken
```php
match (true) {
    'test' => [
'key' => 'value',
    ],
};
```

After:
```php
match (true) {
    'test' => [
        'key' => 'value',
    ],
};
```

With this PR the modifiers are now reported correctly for the following testcase, which is based on the original report in  #4371:

```javascript
class test {
    fieldTest1 = 0;
    #fieldTest2 = 1;

    static fieldTest3 = 2;
    static #fieldTest4 = 3;

    // private
    #test1() {};
    async #test2() {}

    // public
    test3() {}
    async test4() {}

    // static private
    static #test5() {}
    static async #test6() {}

    // static public
    static test7() {}
    static async test8() {}
}
```

